Section2.Para:
Lastly, the latest version of MIMIC, MIMIC-III, was released to the public in August 2015 (see 
                    http://mimic.physionet.org

                  ). MIMIC-III contains approximately 46,000 unique patients, including all MIMIC-II patients. A meaningful future step would be to adapt the visualization tool to MIMIC-III, although this would be more complicated than simply having the tool point to MIMIC-III due to the major differences between MIMIC-II and MIMIC-III schemas. Furthermore, including all NICU data in MIMIC-III would be another way to expand the utility of the tool.
